    "However, a static life cycle is not the ideal evaluation method.",
    "One of the most critical issues in quantifying the carbon footprint of products in the static life cycle is the disregard for time scales.",
    "For example, Røyne et al. (2016) analyzed the life cycle of 101 forestry products and found that 87% of studies believe that biochar is neutral, meaning there is a balance between carbon sequestration.",
    "However, such a conclusion can lead to deviations in the actual value of the static life cycle.",
    "Another method is dynamic life cycle assessment, which considers the time taken for carbon absorption of greenhouse gas emissions."
